// CPUID features leaf-1 advertises that the lifter does NOT yet fully implement.
// Each entry is a conscious, temporary exception checked by
// `cpuid_advertises_only_what_lifts` (OCI-0.T2): a (feature, reason) pair. The test
// fails if CPUID advertises a partially-implemented feature that is NOT listed here,
// so a new advertisement forces either a full implementation or an explicit,
// reasoned waiver. Removing a waiver requires the feature to reach 100% in the
// compat map (wiki/compat/isa-coverage.md). Track: wiki/design/oci-plan.md §OCI-3.
[
    ("MMX", "Zero MMX lifted, but load-bearing: glibc's cpu-features init needs the bit and the glibc-hello corpus test regresses to empty output without it, yet never executes an MMX instruction in the fixture. Do NOT narrow without re-verifying glibc."),
    ("SSE", "Baseline, cannot un-advertise. Remaining gaps are MMX-interop conversions (Cvtpi2ps/Cvtps2pi/Cvttps2pi) and movmskps."),
    ("SSE2", "Baseline, cannot un-advertise. Remaining gaps are the packed int<->float conversion family (cvtdq2ps/cvtps2dq/cvttps2dq/cvtpd2dq/...) and MMX-interop forms."),
    // SSE3 reached 100% lift coverage (addsubp*/haddp*/hsubp* task-244, lddqu, and
    // movddup/movsldup/movshdup task-253), so it no longer needs a waiver.
    ("SSSE3", "pshufb + palignr lifted. Remaining: pabs*, phadd*/phsub*, pmaddubsw, pmulhrsw, psign*. Fully executable for the glibc SSSE3 string routines, which is why SSE4.1/4.2 could be un-advertised (see wiki/decisions/2026-07-06-cpuid-drop-sse4.md)."),
    // SSE4.1 and SSE4.2 are deliberately no longer advertised by cpuid_run — their
    // pcmpistri/pmovzx/ptest/blendv*/round* gaps were live traps for modern glibc,
    // which now falls back to the SSSE3/SSE2 routines above. No waiver needed.
]
